# Notifications

<!-- example shell request -->
```shell
curl -i -H 'X-Apikey: [REQUIRED_APIKEY]' <%= current_page.data.api_url %>/notifications
```

<!-- example response -->
<%= partial 'partials/responses/notifications' %>

Returns a paginated array of all notifications for the user to which the required API key belongs. The __notifier__ property of the response represents the user that took the action that created the notification. The __recipient__ property represents the resource that the notifier acted upon. It will contain a [single video](#single-video) response, a [single photo](#single-photo) response, or a [single user](#single-user) response. The __notification__ property contains a simple prepared sentence that can be used if more advanced parsing of the __notifier__ and/or __recipient__ properties is not required.

### HTTP Request

`GET <%= current_page.data.api_url %>/notifications`

<aside class="warning">
An X-Apikey header containing a valid API key is required to access this endpoint.
</aside>

### Query Parameters

Parameter | Default | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
page      |         | specific page of results
per_page  | 30      | number of results per page

### Error Responses

Code | Message
---- | -------
